# Documentation punctuation

When writing or editing markdown documentation (especially under `docs/`), use **ASCII hyphen-minus** (`-`, U+002D) only. Do not use typographic dashes.

## Do not use

- Em dash: `—` (U+2014)
- En dash: `–` (U+2013)

## Use instead

| Instead of | Use |
|------------|-----|
| Em dash between clauses | ` - ` (space-hyphen-space) |
| En dash in ranges | `-` (e.g. `1-5 min`, `Phase 0-2`) |
| Table option labels | `A - Tune SQL` not `A — Tune SQL` |

## Examples

- Good: `CC Lead MIS Report - Improvement Proposal`
- Bad: `CC Lead MIS Report — Improvement Proposal`

- Good: `read - while keeping all business rules`
- Bad: `read—while keeping` or `read-while keeping` (missing spaces)

- Good: `1-2 weeks`, `2-5 minutes`
- Bad: `1–2 weeks`, `2–5 minutes`

## Compound words

Hyphenated **words** stay joined (no spaces): `on-demand`, `pre-built`, `no-cost`, `short-term`.

Only **clause breaks** use spaced hyphen: `not sufficient - rules stay in SQL`.
